Yes, sir.

00:49:45.535 --> 00:49:48.050
AUDIENCE: Do you think
diversified index funds

00:49:48.050 --> 00:49:51.490
adequately protect the
amateur investor from losers?

00:49:51.490 --> 00:49:54.310
HOWARD MARKS: Well this
is a great question.

00:49:54.310 --> 00:49:55.660
The role of the index fund.

00:49:59.190 --> 00:50:02.550
A lot of people say, I'm going
to take a low risk approach.

00:50:02.550 --> 00:50:05.240
I'm going to invest
in an index fund.

00:50:05.240 --> 00:50:07.870
And they are confused.

00:50:07.870 --> 00:50:11.480
What an index fund does is
it guarantees you performance

00:50:11.480 --> 00:50:13.860
in line with the index.

00:50:13.860 --> 00:50:20.050
So the point is because
of the operation of what's

00:50:20.050 --> 00:50:22.687
called the efficient
market, not many people

00:50:22.687 --> 00:50:23.520
can beat the market.

00:50:23.520 --> 00:50:24.700
It's true.

00:50:24.700 --> 00:50:27.140
Most mutual funds do
not beat the market.

00:50:27.140 --> 00:50:29.990
Most mutual fund investors
would be better off just

00:50:29.990 --> 00:50:32.460
to be in an index fund.

00:50:32.460 --> 00:50:35.730
And in fact, most active
investment schemes

00:50:35.730 --> 00:50:39.180
impose fees that
they don't earn.

00:50:39.180 --> 00:50:41.030
And that is one of
the major reasons

00:50:41.030 --> 00:50:46.810
that most active investment
schemes perform below average.

00:50:46.810 --> 00:50:51.160
So the index fund, which is
called passive investing,

00:50:51.160 --> 00:50:55.910
yes it reduce,
eliminates, the likelihood

00:50:55.910 --> 00:50:58.420
that you fail to keep
up with the index.

00:50:58.420 --> 00:51:00.600
It also, of course,
eliminates the possibility

00:51:00.600 --> 00:51:02.210
that you outperformed the index.

00:51:02.210 --> 00:51:06.210
So you trade away the two sides
of the probability distribution

00:51:06.210 --> 00:51:10.830
for surety that you
get index results.

00:51:10.830 --> 00:51:13.440
But it doesn't eliminate
the risk of the investment.

00:51:13.440 --> 00:51:17.460
It eliminates the risk of
deviating from the index.

00:51:17.460 --> 00:51:21.120
What you have to keep in mind
is that the index fund investor

00:51:21.120 --> 00:51:25.710
loses money every time
the index goes down.

00:51:25.710 --> 00:51:26.210
Why?

00:51:26.210 --> 00:51:30.560
Because there's no value
added to keep it above.

00:51:30.560 --> 00:51:34.160
And by the way, index
investing is a fine thing

00:51:34.160 --> 00:51:37.330
for the average amateur
investor because

00:51:37.330 --> 00:51:39.260
the average amateur
investor, number one,

00:51:39.260 --> 00:51:42.410
can't beat the market
and, number two,

00:51:42.410 --> 00:51:45.160
can't find anybody
or hire anybody

00:51:45.160 --> 00:51:47.160
who can beat the market.

00:51:47.160 --> 00:51:50.640
But the only thing
is he shouldn't think

00:51:50.640 --> 00:51:54.250
that it's a risk-less trade.

00:51:54.250 --> 00:51:58.720
You eliminate what we
call benchmark risk.

00:51:58.720 --> 00:52:02.150
But you retain the risk
of the underlying asset.

